Merrigum is a town in the Goulburn Valley region of Victoria, Australia. The town is in the City of Greater Shepparton local government area, 197 kilometres (122 mi) north of the state capital, Melbourne. At the 2011 census, Merrigum had a population of 672.Merrigum Post Office opened on 1 February 1875.Merrigum fields Australian Rules football and netball teams in the Kyabram District Football Netball League.
Golfers play at the course of the Merrigum Golf Club.